Now, each leather type differs, so does the logo... and of course, the distinction between gold and silver adds a touch of elegance, particularly with the air pressure of saddle leather Barenia. The seventh step emphasizes the importance of color coordination, both within the same leather type and between different leathers, including the color matching of hardware buckles. Typically, the simplest aspect is the color coordination on the inside. Although the eighth step pertains to simple packaging, attention to detail remains crucial. Finally, the ninth step involves careful scheduling of the shipping time, as each style requires a different processing time. c l a u d i a  One of my all time favourite blondes! We all know the tale, discovered in the late 80s at a German discotheque, this one time aspiring lawyer would soon explode into the world of fashion, becoming an ICONIC Supermodel! Her Bridget Bardot likeness soon lead to ELLE covers with Gilles Bensimon, and a career defining campaign for Guess? Jeans, shot by Ellen Von Unwerth, two of the bombshell’s earliest cheerleaders. Her work with both photographers, as well as with the late Herb Ritts, soon caught the attention of Karl Largerfeld, whom made her his longtime Chanel muse, and in turn a Superstar! Claudia was hard to miss throughout the 90s, wether staring on covers of magazines, from Vogue to GQ, to Cosmopolitan and Hello!, everyone wanted a piece of the beautiful blonde. A favourite to all of fashions biggest names, Gianni, Patrick Demarchelier, Lindbergh, Valentino, Arthur Elgort, and many more, it’s safe to say Claudia built one of the most impressive portfolios amongst her contemporaries. Adding to that entrepreneurial endeavours, lucrative multimillion dollar contracts with Revlon and L’Oréal, exercise videos, calendars, and a foray into film, she was also one of the hardest working Supermodels of her time. She, like Cindy, was also one of the few that had crossover appeal, managing to juggle both the worlds of fashion and pop culture, and making men ( straight and gay ) weak at the knees! With so many memorable editorials, covers, campaigns and runway moments, this week is going to be tough in editing down some of my favourites from Claudia, but I’ll give it a shot! Recently celebrating her 53rd birthday, this week I celebrate the iconic, real life Barbie!

anthonyvaccarello en est aujourd’hui le directeur artistique.
